AUDIO: 'Hi, this is Heidi. I\'m interrupting your scrolling to explain exactly how you can create a perfect avatar of yourself with Argill. First, take a nice recent picture of yourself with your head centered, body facing the camera, mouth slightly open, good lighting, and no'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'specific expression. The more it\'s framed like you would for a video, the better the result will be. Then, record 1 minute of audio of yourself with good quality. Talk more quickly and dynamically than you naturally would'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'because AI will slightly degrade the energy in your voice. Go to avatar, click new avatar, then personal avatar, and upload your photo. Click create my voice and upload the recording you made.'

[00:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now discover and pick your styles. This part is the most fun. If you want to edit a style with details like clothing or decoration, you can upload or prompt specific instructions. Here\'s an example. You can also create entirely'

[00:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'new styles just with a simple sentence. Here\'s the result. Now, to create a video, click new video, input your script, and choose how you want us to split it. Then, you get to choose the'

[01:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'kind of B-rolls you want to make your videos more engaging. There are three types of B-rolls. Getty images will input stock videos just like this one. Avatar actions will allow you to have your avatar exist in the world and'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'manipulate objects like this. B-roll positions come in three options, in front like this, split screen, or full screen. You can then pick the type and position of subtitles that you want.'

[01:31] [scene:talk]
